<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
When the Transfer-Encoding header is present the code calls MHD_lookup_connection_value_n(..., &enc, NULL) (i.e. requests the pointer but not the length) and then passes enc to MHD_str_equal_caseless_. If MHD_lookup_connection_value_n returns a pointer into a buffer that is not NUL‑terminated (or if the header value length is not equal to the length of the C string expected), then MHD_str_equal_caseless_ will typically call string.h routines that expect NUL‑terminated strings (e.g. strcmp/strcasecmp) and can read past the end of the header value buffer. This is an out‑of‑bounds access and thus violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17. To avoid the violation the code must use the length returned by the lookup and a length‑bounded comparison (e.g. strncasecmp or an explicit length check) or ensure the returned string is NUL‑terminated before calling NUL‑terminated string functions.
</scenario>
